     Curselast is a door for /X and S!X that displays up to @{fg shine}999@{fg text}(!!!!)
            You can actually scroll up/down with your cursors!!
    @{fg shine}last callers@{fg text} with a gr8 design! Just @{"install" link installation} it and check it out!!!
        Curselast was coded in AmigaE and is fairly fast and small.

                            -magz of megastyle-

@endnode






@node installation

 .
                                                                              .
 :
 :                                                                            :
 : __        _____ .___.   ______ __.              _________. ____________    :
_:(__)_______\\_ _/_|_  l___\\__  // _l______.  _____\\__  //  l____)_  _   /____:_
 :    | __    /_  _ /   /     _ // \\     /_l__\\__     _ //   /    |_    / ___ :
_:____|--/   /-/  //    |--/____/----/__/ \\     /--/____/    |____|/---/\\--/  :
 :      /___/ /___/_____|(rLf)          \\---/__/       l_____|            /___:_
 :                                                                            :
 :                        i n s t a l l a t i o n                             :
 .                                                                            :
                                                                              .

Copy the files in DOORS/ and COMMANDS/ to your directories named DOORS:
and BBS:COMMANDS/ Then put in let's say your LOGON.TXT and/or one of your
BULL<xx>.TXT files:

-----[ cut ]------

~
~CC_curselast|

-----[ cut ]------


Curselast requires to be updated in the
logoffbatch of your bbs. therefore add to your logoffbatch:

-----[ cut ]------

DOORS:-mgs!-curselast/curseupdate <node>

-----[ cut ]------

Where <node> stands for the node the logoffbatch will
be executed by on logoff.


Edit the icon "DOORS:-mgs!-curselast/curseupdate.info" to suit your needs:
                  .
SYSOP=<sysop>     | Where <sysop> can be 1 (display sysop/local logins) or 0 (ignore sysop/local logins)
LINES=<lines>     | Where <lines> can be 16-999 which is the number of last callers you want to display
                  | (16 = No scrolling)
                  '

That should be it :)

For S!X users.. just make a new line in your bbs.cmd file.. you know how ;)


@endnode





